The paper focuses on the development of a system for robots to autonomously navigate and map complex, unstructured environments using a localized RGB-D camera. This involves the use of higher level entities such as individual object instances to build a functional understanding of the environment. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of computer vision techniques for segmentation and semantic predictions, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques for data association and semantic classification, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the development of a system for semantic mapping, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category.
